quran[10]{c,v,t,f}:
  21,1,"The reckoning of the people has drawn near, yet they are turning away heedlessly.",""
  21,2,"Whenever new revelation comes to them from their Lord, they listen to it in jest,",""
  21,3,"with their hearts heedless. The wrongdoers whisper to one another in secret, “Is this but a human being just like yourselves? Will you then follow his magic, although you openly see?”",""
  21,4,"He said, “My Lord knows every word spoken in the heavens and earth, for He is the All-Hearing, the All-Knowing.”",""
  21,5,"Yet they say, “This [Qur’an] is a set of jumbled dreams! Rather, he has fabricated it! Rather, he is a poet! So let him bring us a sign just as the earlier messengers were sent with<sup>1</sup>.”","[1] Such as the staff of Moses (عليه السلام), the camel of Salih (عليه السلام) and the like."
  21,6,"Not a single town We destroyed before them had believed<sup>2</sup>. Will they then believe?","[2] Although they witnessed signs and miracles."
  21,7,"We did not send before you [O Prophet] except men to whom We gave a revelation, so [O people] ask the People of the Scriptures if you do not know.",""
  21,8,"We did not give them bodies that needed no food<sup>3</sup>, nor were they immortal.","[3] Such as the angels."
  21,9,"Then We fulfilled Our promise to them: We saved them<sup>4</sup> and those whom We willed, and destroyed those who transgressed all bounds.","[4] After they conveyed the message."
  21,10,"We have sent down to you [O people] a Book in which there is honor for you<sup>5</sup>. Do you not then understand?","[5] As you have been mentioned and addressed in the Qur’an, or there is a reminder for you in it."
